      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt chocolate and beat eggs",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C (160°C fan). Line a 20 cm square tin with baking paper. Melt {{dark-chocolate}} and {{unsalted-butter}} together in a bowl over barely simmering water, or in the microwave in 30-second bursts, stirring between each. Leave to cool for 5 minutes. In a separate large bowl, beat {{eggs}} and {{caster-sugar}} with an electric whisk for 3 to 4 minutes until pale and thickened to the ribbon stage. Beat in {{vanilla-extract}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fold and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the cooled chocolate mixture into the egg mixture and fold together gently, don't beat. Sift in {{plain-flour}}, {{cocoa-powder}}, and {{salt-table}} and fold again until just combined. Pour into the tin and bake for 22 to 25 minutes until the edges are set and the centre still has a slight wobble when the tin is shaken. A skewer 2 cm from the edge should come out with a few moist crumbs. Leave to cool completely in the tin before cutting, at least 1 hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
